The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Ruskin Bond

 Author

 To an extent, yes. It has created some new readers. But there are young readers as well who have not read Harry Potter. Actually, the percentage of serious book-readers has never been high. In my class at Bishop Cotton School, in Simla, there were two-three of us among the 35 who were into reading. The others just read comics. There were no distractions then of the TV or the Internet. Perhaps there are more book-readers now in schools. The biggest contribution of Harry Potter is drawing the attention of the publishers to the possibilities of the children?s book section. So, you have more titles and new authors coming up.




